dcterms:description: A synthetic dataset consisting of trajectory member instances (trajectory steps), where one group member has different attributes such as 'Person', 'Sequence Step', 'XCoord', and 'YCoord'. A GAD-label is defined for one complete group (trajectory) stating whether a group (a trajectory) is anomalous (1) or normal (0).
dcterms:title: Synthetic Dataset

dcterms:description: A dataset from Amazon describing walk or driving paths, utilized for trajectory anomaly detection.
dcterms:title: Amazon Dataset

dcterms:description: A dataset from Brightkite with location-based social-networking provider trajectory data, used for trajectory anomaly detection.
dcterms:title: Brightkite Dataset
